******
[2] Pakistan (Punjab - Muzaffargarh), 7-month-old male
Date: Sun 15 Dec 2019
Source: ARY News [abridged, edited]
https://arynews.tv/en/another-polio-case-emerges-in-punjab-tally-up-to-104/


Another polio case has been reported in Punjab on Sunday [15 Dec 2019], taking the tally of such cases across the country to 104 this year [2019], ARY News reported.

According to the Health Ministry, the polio case was reported from the Muzaffargarh city of Punjab province. The authorities said that a 7-month-old baby boy in Muzaffargarh was diagnosed with the crippling disease, adding that the minor was not vaccinated against the virus.

